clinicalDescription: Overview: Prelabor rupture of membranes (PROM) refers to membrane rupture before the onset of uterine contractions. A subset of this is Preterm PROM (PPROM) refers to PROM before 37+0 weeks of gestation. PPROM occurs in upto 3% of pregnancies. Presentation: 'Gush' of fluid or leaking of fluid. Plan: direct visual exam of cervix, digital exam should be avoided to prevent infection. Tests for amniotic fluid. Prognosis: Good in the absence of infection. Most deliver within one week, even in PPROM.
